This paper addresses the problem of phrase grounding, which involves both computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). However, the paper also utilizes contextualized word-level and sentence-level embeddings extracted from a character-based language model, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel approach using a multi-level multimodal attention mechanism, which involves machine learning and could fit into categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with multimodal data, which could also place it in the cs.MM (Multimedia) category.
